        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 3:29PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 328 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 16 miles west of Lima to 13
miles northeast of Monida. Movement was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lima, Monida, Grant, Dell, Beaverhead Rock State Park, Bannack Pass,
Red Rock Pass, Lakeview, Clark Canyon, and Snowline.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
